cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.CE, cs.NE

This paper deals with the challenges of processing large datasets in genome-wide association studies. The methods presented involve handling large amounts of data and distributing it across multiple systems, which are common topics in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), distributed computing (cs.DC), databases (cs.DB), computational biology (cs.CE), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
